            "answer_text": "Firstly, they can be stored as glycogen in your liver and your muscles. Glycogen is a polymer of glucose molecules and is broken down as soon as your blood sugar level drops to low, to supply your cells with energy. If your glycogen storage is filled up, carbs are converted to fat in your fatty tissue. Anyway, both mechanisms happen at the same time. As soon as you eat carbs, your muscle and fat cells absorb glucose molecules, triggered by insulin. ",
